results.name: Fluctuations of the number of cubefree integers not exceeding 2^n
comment: The asymptotic density of cubefree integers is the reciprocal of Apery's constant 1/zeta(3) = 0.83190737258... The number of cubefree integers not exceeding N is thus roughly N/zeta(3). When N is a power of 2, this sequence gives the difference between the actual number (A160113) and that linear estimate (rounded to the nearest integer).
link: G. P. Michon, Reciprocal of Apery's constant.
G. P. Michon, On the number of cubefree integers not exceeding N.
xref: A004709 (cubefree integers). A160112 & A160113 (counting cubefree integers).
results.author: _Gerard P. Michon_, May 06 2009
